ten (auch im Hinblick auf Grammatikalisierungsprozesse), Aspekte der maschinellen Sprachverarbeitung präpositionaler Elemente sowie ihre Bedeutungen aus der Sicht der Kognitiven Linguistik.  aThis volume contains papers presented at a workshop held at the 18th annual meeting of Deutsche Gesellschaft für Sprachwissenschaft in 1996. The articles contained in this volume focus on the lexical vs. functional categoryhood of prepositional elements, their syntactic and semantic properties (also with respect to grammaticalization), aspects of automatic language processing and the meanings of prepositional elements in cognitive linguistics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEnglish languagexPrepositions. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxPrepositions. 4aPräposition. 4aPräpositionalphrase. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBoas, Hans Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroschart, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuyckens, Hubert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaftka, Brigitta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaumann, Dagmar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeibig, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJirjahn, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMertens, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRadden, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchierholz, Stefan J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchulz, Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWege, Barbara, econt